Hello,

- To run this code you need the following:
	1- if you don't have c++ installed, install c++ using :sudo apt-get install build-essential
	2- if you don't have opencv installed please follow this link to install opencv : https://docs.opencv.org/trunk/d7/d9f/tutorial_linux_install.html
- In order to run the code you can do the following:
	1- clone this repo and write in terminal : cd MyCujoo_task
	2- compile the file using : g++ find_shapes.cpp -o out `pkg-config --libs --cflags opencv`
        3- run the following command: ./out <path/to/the/image>.png


